\int \sin x\cos x \;dx.
\sin2x=2\sin x\cos x
\int \sin x\cos x \;dx=\int \frac{\sin2x}{2}dx=-\frac{1}{4}\cos2x+C
u
u=\sin x
du=\cos x\,dx
\int\sin x\cos x\,dx=\int u\,du=\frac12u^2+C=\frac12\sin^2x+C\;.
\int f'(x)f(x)^ndx=\frac{f(x)^{n+1}}{n+1}+C\;,\;\;-1\ne n\in\Bbb R
